description:
&lt;p&gt;Are you looking for a leadership opportunity? Are you an experienced Band 5 Community Nurse looking for development or a Band 6 Nurse who wishes to change direction?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Postholder will offer direction, leadership and professional supervision to unregistered and registered nursing staff in the team. Aiming to enable people to maximise their independence and optimise their quality of life whilst remaining at home or their preferred place of care and reducing the risk of admission to hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Working with a Nurse Team Manager (Community) and using leadership skills and knowledge you will lead and manage a team of registered and unregistered nurses and other staff who may be working in the team. You will be assess patients with complex health care needs, complete appropriate documentation and develop care plans as required. Monitoring and maintaining standards of care for all those on the caseload will be an essential part of your role as well as supporting the team to do this as part of the delivery of care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The postholder will also be expected to contribute to regular completion of audit to inform future practice.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate must be a very experienced Community nurse with current clinical competencies relating to Community Nursing. They must be able to demonstrate knowledge and understanding of current issues relating to Primary Care, Community Nursing, Social Care and other community services.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an exciting time in community nursing with the introduction of a new electronic patient record across the RDE Trust, this will allow new ways of working and promote innovation and improved communication for Health and Social Care Teams. As a B6 you would lead and support the team in the implementation of this system and it’s daily use to enhance patient care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate would be expected to be educated to degree level, provide evidence of Continual Professional Development and have a teaching/assessing qualification or equivalent experience. Part of the role would be as a Practice Assessor or Supervisor to Student Nurses/TAP/AN. Prescribing and leadership qualifications relevant to community nursing would be desirable. If this has not been achieved then the successful candidate would be expected to complete these qualifications as part of their development in this role and opportunities would be provided to do this.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our vision is to provide safe, high quality seamless services delivered with courtesy and respect. To achieve our vision we expect all our staff to uphold our Trust values. Our Trust values are: &lt;br /&gt; Honesty, Openness &amp; Integrity&lt;br /&gt; Fairness&lt;br /&gt; Inclusion &amp; Collaboration&lt;br /&gt; Respect &amp; Dignity&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;***Preference will be given to staff with ‘Priority’ and &#39;At Risk&#39; status including NHS At Risk staff throughout Devon.***&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;DUE TO THE ANTICIPATED HIGH NUMBER OF APPLICATIONS FOR THIS POST WE RESERVE THE RIGHT TO CLOSE THE VACANCY BEFORE THE CLOSING DATE.&lt;/p&gt;
